The problem is supply relative to thead size/specificity. Talking stories was much easier when there were tens of concurrent, active stories and strong odds that most readers had read all of them. Now the supply is so high that its statistically unlikely that more than one or two people reading the thread at a given time have read the same story recently, which makes it tough to chain more than a few posts about it. Not really a good or bad thing, but I can't think of a way around it. Sure, the thread could generally talk more about writing, but most of the time it won't be about a story you know simply because statistics
